HARRY Kane joined the 100 club for Premier League goals after his dramatic last-gasp penalty which earned a point for Tottenham against Liverpool on Sunday.The England striker became the second fastest player to reach the milestone, behind Alan Shearer, when he stepped up from 12 yards at Anfield to make it 2-2.Kane, held his nerve to hit the back of the net after missing an earlier penalty, which would have given Spurs a 2-1 lead.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The forward said he was desperate for a reprieve after his tame effort was saved by Liverpool goalkeeper Loris Karius before Mohamed Salah scored to put Liverpool ahead in the 91st minute.Kane, who scored his 22nd goal of the season as well as his 100th Premier League goal in 141 appearances, told Sky Sports Main Event: "I was praying."You don't expect to especially when it's deep into stoppage time but thankfully I got the second chance and I'm delighted to get my 100th goal in the Premier League."It's great to be in that 100 club."It was nice to get something out of the game after a roller coaster of emotions."Following the England star's landmark, Nike unveiled its special-edition Nike Hypervenom 3 HK boots, which will be worn by Kane in his next match.Just 100 pairs of boots, designed in the star's favourite white and blue colours, will be available to buy at a later date.Kane became the 26th player to reach 100 Premier League goals, moving second ahead of Sergio Aguero (147) in the list of fastest centurions.Alan Shearer notched his century of top flight goals in just 124 matches.Thierry Henry (160) and Ian Wright (173) make up the top five ahead of Robbie Fowler (175) and Les Ferdinand (178). -REUTERS